Key Match Events: Andrew Heaney snapped an eight-start winless streak
Marcus Semien hit Dana's first pitch for his sixth leadoff homer this season and 30th of his career
Ezequiel Duran's homer was his third of the season, the first since June 11
Kirby Yates earned his 29th save in 30 chances
Post-Match Reflections: Andrew Heaney said he was'very happy' about the win and thanked his teammates for the support
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Rangers won three of four games against the Angels to match a season-best four consecutive series won
The defending World Series champions (70-74) have climbed within four games of.500 for the first time since July 30
Others: Texas chased 20-year-old right-hander Caden Dana (1-1) 11 batters into his second major league start
Dana gave up five runs on seven hits, including three home runs, and left with the bases loaded with none out in the second inning
